content.detailedDescription:
driving back on hwy. 13- 2 miles south of the missouri river bridge-- i looked northwest-   2 bright lights- almost like fireworks were slowly ascending- straight up-  like asteroids- bright and seemingly burning- almost as if witnessing a rocket-- except for there wasn't a long tail- it was very hard to guage the distance-   one light was ahead but off to the side of the other light at a slight offset angle-  then one slowly dimmed as it reached an altitude where it seemed to stop ascending- then the other-- also stopped ascending as if it had run out of fuel and then dimmed out-- burnt out seemingly--  as if there were rockets leaving the atmosphere- except for getting brighter it just burnt out-- this seemed to happen towards the middle of the sky-- so if it was a long ways away it could've been a very high altitude--  but when i first spotted it- it seemed to only be about 20'-25'degrees up-   i have seen the space station before and that was also 2 lights-  this was very alarming and i drove towards the river on a dirt road but could see no traces.  i called local dispatch and alerted them but they seemed to only respond that they would be watching for more phone calls-  the lights didn't come back or move in any way-- just straight up and gone- 
i would enjoy helping to monitor and respond if you ever need me in any way-  the glasgow airforce base is northwest of me- and i know they do test flights-  perhaps they picked it up on radar? 

sincerely,
jesse sansaver

content.detailedDescription:
On wednesday night 1/27/16, my wife was in our upstairs bedroom.  she told me what she saw:  a bright, concentrated "white light" shown through two of our windows; the light was rectangular in shape, approximately 10'x 10'.  the light "flashed" several time like a strobe light and then it went away.  she also said the white light had "blue" coloring in it.
     what makes her experience even more bizarre is that it coincides with an almost duplicate experience i had about two months prior: when she had her experience, i was downstairs doing some paperwork.  when i came up, about 11 p.M. she detailed the event to me, as described above. when i had my experience, i was outside playing my ukulele about 11 p.M. with me, extremely focused, concentrated white light shown on the exact same two windows of our upstairs bedroom.
     the "white light" flashed, kind of like a strobe light.  it did this "on and off" three or four times and then the light was gone.  what was also very odd, was that there was no source, that i could see, from where the light originated.  i told my wife about my event and now, about two months later, she had the same thing happen.
     what makes our events even stranger, is that about four to six months earlier, i was, once again, sitting outside, playing my ukulele, at approximately the same time, 11 p.M.  the night time sky was totally clear.  very low, overhead, maybe 100', coming directly towards me, a very large, black ufo appeared.  it was "silent."  it made no sounds.  it had three red lights, but i could not actually tell what its shape was, because the sky was clear, but dark, and the ufo was black in color.
     i called out to my wife and told her to "hurry downstairs, come outside and 'see' this thing."  she did so, and "together" we saw the craft move extremely, slow; it almost seemed to be "hovering" overhead and then it kind of glided away at a slow speed and then, a minute or so later, it moved away very quickly and then it was gone.  we talked about it for a long time afterwards.  
     over time, we have recounted the ufo encounter to a few of our friends, but we have never mentioned the "white flashing lights."  we obviously do not know if the "lights" and the ufo sighting are related; but we do know, these things have never happened to us before.
content.summary: focused,bright white light thru windows.

content.detailedDescription:
Detailed description of the ufo event:
it was an unusual night with fog on the river, warm weather when it should be cold and/or snowing. the fog stayed close to the ground reaching a few stories in the air at most. i went to town to buy something and made my purchase right after they called "shoppers, you have 10 minutes..." so i know it was about that approximate time when i arrived home.

i drove the rural way home along the river. i live very close to the river. when i was getting very close to home, i noticed a cluster of 3 orange lights very close to me over neighbor a's yard across the road from me or right on the river; that's how close we are to the river.

i live in a rural area so the neighbors' houses are a few hundred feet from each other.

this cluster of orange lights was about helicopter height. there was no structure to support the lights or i could not see the structure even though it was above the fog. the lights beamed a little. they looked exactly like the street lights on my road with the same color, same size, and same slight beam of light except that i was looking at a cluster of 3 lights. the orange lights stayed stationery as i drove down my road and into my drive way.

i had never seen orange lights this low in the sky and there was no structure present as to why the lights would be there.

i parked the car in the back of the house and ran to a front corner of the house to see if the cluster of lights were still there. it was but it started slowly moving in a straight line, moving closer to me.

i ran the short distance to get my sister to come outside and look at "this big plane". there is frequent unusual activity in the sky here so she put on shoes and came running out.

what i witnessed before she got outside was a giant black triangle shape reveal itself over neighbor b's house which is the 2nd house from me to the west.  the triangle went in a straight line over neighbor b's house, it backed up a little bit like it changed it's mind and then traveled in straight line directly at me.

it had descended to top-of-tree height by now. was it going to crash? why is it so low? what is it? i was scared and wanted to run somewhere but where to? i was in the middle of the yard and if i ran in the house and it crashed, that was not a great place to go. if it was looking for me, it had already spotted me.

my sister arrived outside and looked up to see it just as it started to travel in a straight line from neighbor b's house.

it had great height to it. it was not a flat triangle. it was several stories height. it was flat black or dark gray color. it was way larger than a football field. it was enormous. it was so close, detail was clear of it's structure, size and lights.

it turned on it's bottom lights on it's way over to my yard. it had varied bottom lights. outlining the craft were small white lights with 3 sets of red/green lights. in the middle was a large triangle area of what looked like white led lights glowing. the pattern of these white lights was indescribable.  was it showing clouds or transparency?

as the triangle front endpoint arrived at the yard, it started emitting this hydraulic engine type of noise, loud, roaring, and bumpy sounding. i'm familiar with hydraulic engine sounds as to the many boats on the river here and that's the closest i would describe it. 

(i had heard that same loud engine noise travel the entire sky a few weeks prior to this event from inside my house. i ran outside to sight what would make that loud noise and i could not see it.)

it scared me so i didn't look when it was directly overhead but my sister watched it. i could still see it even when not looking directly at it. the white lights glowed. i looked up at it after several seconds, and it was still there, hovering/moving very slowly. 

i got a good look at the bottom lights at this time but still don't know how to describe the white lights in the middle, what pattern the white lights were. maybe it was a transparent area as well as being lit up.

if she hadn't come outside when she did, i was on my way to hiding. instead, she came outside and yelled at it to get out of here. the noise was loud enough that i couldn't hear her yelling at it. i felt responsible for calling her outside to see it and i didn't want it to get her so i stayed while making useless getaway plans and getaway movements.

she seen it approach but she didn't realize how close it was because of night depth perception issues. i wouldn't have yelled at it but she did and i'm glad. i hope that's what made it go away.

we watched it until the end of the triangle shape went over us. it turned off it's sound and lights after it went over us. the black triangle disappeared into the black night and we didn't stand around outside after that. when the sky is heavy with water like that, you can't see the stars, it's just very dark.

we still marvel over seeing this triangle. we talk about it every day. i'm nervous when i have to frequently walk back and forth between the 2 houses on the lot here. you don't want to see it again but you want to. such a mixture of feelings, it was a major event for me.

it would be nice and way easier to believe that it is human military but i don't know if that is plausible. now we joke about how it was a good thing she came outside before it vacuumed me up and that two of us was too many for it to beam up. i nervously laugh.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change
content.summary: stationary orange lights reveal to be a giant triangle that glide directly over us.

content.detailedDescription:
About 2110 hrs. on 16 mar 13, i was in the backyard, waiting for my elderly dog to do his business. i usually star-gaze, so this is what i was doing when i noticed a huge triangular craft just to the north of my neighborhood, about 60 ft. in the air. it made absolutely no noise and had no lights of any kind on it. the craft was moving very slowly. having been in the military for quite a while, i can gauge the size of craft pretty well, so i'd say this craft was easily 400 - 500 ft. long per side. it moved in a south-easterly direction, again - extremely slowly and with no noise, and then just vanished. i brought my dog inside and wanted to call someone, a friend or relative, and tell them what i saw, but was afraid of being laughed at. i'm still a bit afraid of being laughed at, but finally decided to tell mufon about this. i don't really expect anything to be done about it. 
one other thing.....
rio rancho, where i live, is just northeast of kirtland afb and southeast of dulce. not just myself, but several of my friends and relatives also often see black helicopters (with blacked-out windows) flying from kirtland afb to dulce. i don't know if this triangular craft i saw was from dulce or not, but it may have been.
content.summary: Ufo moved slowly for approx. 7 min., then abruptly vanished. didn't fly off, but vanished.

content.detailedDescription: I was drinking coffee on my porch swing when i saw motion in my right peripheral vision. i turned my head and saw a large sphere passing from west to east. the sphere appeared to be a ball of energy.  it was very bright and intense.  i expected to hear thunder or an explosion as it passed me, or to feel heat or wind.  i experienced none of those things.  the sphere continued moving at a steady pace until it entered the woods across the road from my property, to the east.  the sphere just disappeared into the woods.  there was no leaf or tree\brush movement, nor any indication that anything had passed into the woods.  i walked the path where i saw the sphere move, expecting to see singe marks from the intense energy the sphere exhibited but saw nothing.  my most profound reaction was surprise that something that appeared so intensely full of bright energy made no sound, gave off no heat, and moved so smoothly\determinedly on its own.  the sphere simply moved into the woods as though by osmosis.
content.summary: Observed a sphere moving slowly in a straight path

content.detailedDescription:
On a warm night in 1984, we were sitting outside in the yard talking at our family farm in central texas. i cannot remember the exact date, but it was a pleasant, starlit and moonlit night, perhaps in the early spring or fall. we could see well enough to walk around outside, so there must have been a full moon or a nearly full moon. 

my two dogs suddenly began barking and running off toward a the neighbor's pasture, which is located to the north side of our farm. the property line runs only 30 yards or so from where we were sitting, and a barbed wire fence separates the two farms. the other property was pretty large, perhaps 200 or more acres, with a mix of oak trees, mesquite thickets, and grassy areas scattered with weeds, brush, prickly pear, and brier patches. nobody lived there except a herd of cows, so the pasture next to the fence was an overgrown tangle of brush at the time. my dogs ran through the fence wires and into the neighbor's pasture, still barking, and i walked over there to see what had caused them to bark. 

these were very vigilant, fiercely protective watchdogs -- the kind of dogs that kept people in their cars until i called the dogs off. they weren't prone to running off barking at rabbits or small animals, but they did chase the neighbor's cows if they got too close to the fence. if a person were to get close to that fence, that would be as far as he would get without getting dog-bit. so when those dogs barked and ran toward the fence, i followed them to see why they were agitated. i fully expected to see them chasing the neighbor's cows, but all i saw was the vague outline of trees, weeds, and bushes in the moonlight, and the two dogs charging back towards me. they shot through the fence and stood beside me, no longer barking but looking toward the neighboring pasture. it was really strange behavior for them. 

at that point i heard a very weird sound, like a baby crying, which was coming from the pasture. the sound lasted only a few seconds and then stopped. the dogs didn't react except to perk their ears a bit. no baby would be in the woods at night, but a rabbit makes a similar sound when it thinks it's about to die, so i thought something must have killed a rabbit. obviously it was not my dogs that killed it because they were now beside me.

while still wondering about the weird noise, i was startled to see a bright red light suddenly appear, hovering above the ground perhaps 12 to 15 feet, just 50 to 75 feet beyond the fence. it was like an orb that glowed red but had a brighter beam of red light that was slowly rotating. it clearly illuminated the trees and undergrowth below and around the light-object, and when the bright beam rotated in my direction, it was blindingly bright. i could see nothing below or above it to which the light might be connected -- it was just a "light" that just hovered there, silently. it was not in a location where you would expect any people to be at that time of night (or any time), and my dogs would have continued to bark if there were people so close to the fence. i do not think a vehicle could be driven to that spot, and there was no sound or noise -- you can hear vehicle sounds long before you see the vehicle, at that location.

i went to get the others, and three of my relatives ended up witnessing this, in addition to myself. we watched the revolving red light for 10 to 15 more minutes, excitedly discussing it, wondering what it was. we were too freaked out to think of getting a camera. nobody went closer because you'd have to climb the barbed wire fence and then walk through a very overgrown, rattlesnake-infested and cactus-laden pasture to get closer to the light, and we could see it very clearly from where we stood. nobody saw anything to which this light was attached, and it remained about 12 to 15 feet off the ground at all times, steadily rotating its bright red beam. then suddenly, the light went out.

about 30 seconds later the light re-appeared, but in a new location. in total silence, it had moved to the northeast part of the pasture, which was heavily overgrown with mesquite trees. this was probably 200 to 300 yards further away and the mesquites were so thick it was hard to see the light, yet it still lit up the trees around it as it rotated. we began walking along the fence to get closer, but when we began to close in on it, the light went out again. so we started to go back to the house. then we saw the light again, now in the northwest part of the pasture, and very far away from its previous position. once again it had moved in total silence. we walked in that direction for a few steps and the light went out again, and after that we never saw it again.

i don't know what this light or object was. if it was related to human activity, i don't know how they got to that first location or the other locations, one of which was virtually inaccessible, in total silence and in a matter of seconds between locations. or how any person could be in that first location, so close to the fence, without getting bit by my dogs (one of my dogs was notorious about biting people who she deemed to be "trespassers.") also why had no humans been seen in the illuminated area created by the hovering light and the moonlight. the light seemed to be an object hovering in space, 12 to 15 feet off the ground. it illuminated the ground and there was nothing under it except trees and brush. nor could we see anything above it.

even a 4-wheel-drive vehicle would probably be impossible to drive in that area and would have made a lot of noise. walking through acres and acres of overgrown property at night would be very strange and foolish. besides this, it was rare to ever see people on that property. nobody lived there and people hardly ever ever walked around or drove around on that farm, or hunted or did anything else on that property. certainly not at night. besides this, any such activity would have made noise, but there was no noise associated with the hovering light. our farmhouse was adjacent to that pasture, with windows overlooking it. it had been about 10 years since i personally had seen a person step foot on that part of the neighboring property.

was this a ufo? i don't know what the heck we saw, just that we saw it. if it was hovering as it seemed to be, then yes it was a ufo. at the time, we had no idea what it was and we still don't. we never reported it. there is actually a history of at least one reported ufo sighting and a cattle mutilation in the area, and a couple of other incidents have happened on the farm, but this incident was witnessed by more people and we had a much closer view of this rotating-red-light object. mufon can contact me for more info on the other things.
content.summary: We saw a hovering, rotating red light illuminating the ground, which twice turned off and then moved, with no sound.

content.detailedDescription:
Well, to begin with i was sitting at the corner of my couch half heartedly watching a movie.   then lights caught my eye from my western-facing living room balcony.   this is a bit normal since i live in a medical center. so, i see helicopters quite a bit from my balcony. it honestly didn't seem right, but i casually kept an eye on it.  there were too many bright lights coming in from the nnw.  like 3-4 headlights from a car over the treetops and buildings.  i still didn't think it was too unusual since we have a lot of helicopters flying in from various locations to the hospitals in my area. 

then i felt something was off, so i went out onto the balcony to get a better look.   i felt that what i was looking at was "off" and it was too graceful and slow to be a helicopter or airplane.  so, i knocked on my son's window to get a second opinion.   since that time the object changed direction and headed towards the west.  i begin recording at this on my phone.  by that time my son appeared on the balcony with me.  i was still convinced that it was a plane.   we took noticed of a jet following, according to our perspective, above and behind the object keeping a constant pace with it.  the lights on the object were flashing randomly, and a blue light turned on and this convinced my son this was more than a plane.  it flew low to the horizon from our 2nd floor perspective.

i lost visual on the object due to buildings and tree branches.  my son however ran after out of our apartment to get a better look.  i followed.  by that time the object was heading from a sw direction and headed east.  like its flight path was more of a curve.  my son went up the street to follow it, and according to him it just disappeared mid-flight.  this frightened him more than anything.  needless to say that there was a sense of disbelief and excitement.  i'm still not sure what we witnessed that night.  the jet escort followed this object up until it disappeared.  for a while afterwards the sky was "crowded" with jets and helicopters.  my son was able to get a good visual before it disappeared, and quickly sketched the object our with the layout of its lights.
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: It was a blinking object being followed by a jet.

content.detailedDescription: Traveling on bethel church road heading towards logan, after leaving south hills village.  was approaching logan road on the left and saw lights from 3 objects in the sky in front of me slightly to the right, where there are not normally lights.  pointed them out to my husband and slowed the vehicle down to 5 mph or less to observe.  put the windows down and could hear a thrumming sound.  the objects were low and moving slowly, and they crossed over the vehicle from the left (which was disconcerting because when first observed they appeared to be to my right).  they passed out of my view in the driver's seat, and my husband observed the 2 smaller objects veer to the right, and the larger object, in his words, "winked out." it was dark and the road doesn't have any areas to pull over. when i first saw the objects, i was confused because they didn't have any red or green lights indicative of an airplane.  there appeared to be mist or smoke around them, but there was no mist or smoke ground level, nor any precipitation.  we weren't frightened, just wishing to have had a better, longer look at them.  this all transpired within a minute or two.  upon arriving home, i called a good friend of mine who grew up in an aviation family and is also a pilot and described the lights hoping she could tell me what type of plane it might be.  after my description, she said "those were no planes."  she told me to look up "phoenix lights" and the large object looked very much like some of the photos on that site.  thank you.
content.summary: Observed object in sky - straight line of 6 white round lights.  two other objects with 2 round white lights each.

content.detailedDescription: In august of 1997. a friend of mine and i had went to 1000 steps to watch the sun set. around 8 pm we seen something rise out of the ocean. brite white and yellow in color. at first we thought it was maybe a boat on fire? we watched it for several min. then all of a sudden then light seemed to start moving towards us at a fast rate of speed. i grabbed my friends hand and told her we should go! before we made it to the bottom of the steps the lights were on top of us. we were hit with this bright beam of light. as bright as a spot light. the next thing i remember is we both woke up on the side of the bank. with her in my arms. we got up and dident say a word all the way home. when i got her home i noticed a hour and ten min of time were missing. i just spoke to my friend a year ago for the first time. and she mentioned that night. and one other thing that's strange? both our eyes were blue when this happened and now they are green. and both our eyes changed with in a six month time span. thank you for your time.
content.summary: Came out of the water then came up to us suddenly.
